==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cosmolabe
<hw>Cos"mo*labe</hw> <pr>(k?z"m?-l?b)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ko`smos</grk> the world + <grk>lamba`nein</grk> to take: cf. F.
<ets>cosmolade</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument resembling the
astrolabe, formerly used for measuring the angles between heavenly
bodies; -- called also <altname>pantacosm</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cosmolatry</ent>⟦br⟧
